Program: Free Thinking
Title: Umberto Eco
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b06qmcqn
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 1 Dec 2015
Italian author Umberto Eco is in conversation with Matthew Sweet. Eco is the author of essays, novels, childrens' books and criticism including his best-selling story The Name of the Rose. His new novel Numero Zero explores the lure of conspiracy theories and the power of the media. Numero Zero by Umberto Eco is out now. (Main image: Umberto Eco, (c) Leonardo Cendamo). Show less